I"Ð<h4 id="giffigift-for-future-inventors">GIFFI:Gift For Future Inventors</h4>

<p><img src="http://localhost:4000/assets/img/project/giffi/GIFFI POSTER.png" alt="img0" /></p>

<p><img src="http://localhost:4000/assets/img/project/giffi/giffi_robots.jpg" alt="img1" /></p>

<p><img src="http://localhost:4000/assets/img/project/giffi/passive parts.jpg" alt="img2" /></p>

<p>GIFFI is a computationally enhanced construction kit that enables children to build kinetic forms through purposeful play and discovery.It offers three types of movement blocks: axial / rotational, hinge / swinging, and extension / telescoping.</p>

<p>User can set the blockâ€™s speed and range of movement with programming board. Adding a rotational block makes the squiggly snake robot turn its head.</p>

<p>GIFFI project was accepted to show case at the Sixth International Conference on Tangible, Embedded and Embodied Interaction (TEI 2012). The full paper can be viewed <a href="http://localhost:4000/assets/img/project/giffi/121-Wu.pdf">here</a></p>

